## Keep environment variable MAN_DISABLE_SECCOMP to work arround `man` `seccomp`
## bug when using `sudo` so it is passed to APT and eventually to `man`.
## See /etc/X11/Xsession.d/50hardened-malloc for more information.
Defaults:ALL env_keep += "MAN_DISABLE_SECCOMP"
